reviews.text: This church was built more than 150 years ago and hence has historical significance. Even though it is situated at a crowded junction, you can feel the peace once you walk down the path from the entrance to the church. On stepping into it you get to see a glimpse of an era that has been preserved. The peaceful and holy atmosphere is most evident in the afternoon which was the time I chose to visit it.

Right at the heart of the city, this church is a perfect location for worship. Tree covered campus, ample parking space, neatly maintained gardens and buildings. Church is pretty old, still with the old chairs and benches, same old walls and floor. Under renovation now, a new look is expected.

Resting place for the traffic police men while they're not very busy, a breathing space for them.

It was built in 1851, for the British Regiment stationed in Bangalore. 
Built in the English Renaissance style, the church can accommodate 
700 people and is regarded as the largest "military" church in southern India. 
It has a congregation of over 450 families
The church was consecrated on 25 July 1852 and opened on 8 August, 1852. 
The original estimate of the construction was ₹27,000 (US$380)
After Independence, the church was taken over by the Christian Indian Military personnel 
and their families. It was called Holy Trinity Garrison Pastorate then.
The walls were lined with ornate marble murals and tablets, which spoke about 
great men and women who toiled for the church. They Used to conduct many programs for youth especially Troika. They have a best team for youth. On March 10th they conducted the Peace Rally for the Pulwama Terrorist Attack. Really its a good experience for me. I Love this Church

When I moved to Bangalore, my fiancé was going here so he took me here. It was away from where we stay so we started checking other Tamil places nearby but now we are regularly going there. It’s worth traveling there. Best place to worship, such a nice priest. They have a good worshipping culture. You can feel Almighty’s presence there. #myfavchurch
Always a church with deep history and architecture gives a nostalgic feeling. This Tamil church surely is one of the churches which makes me feel at home and gives me a blessed experience.

Products are very expressive even with a value card. I could just go down valley and get a better affordable price. However, the major flaw with Aspen city market is the employees and how terrible they are trained. The problem must be the management because else who trains the employees? If the employees performance lacks due to poor training, and the manager trains the employees; therefore, the managers are not training the employees correctly. I have heard criticism that the HR's treat them poorly and unjustly. Even heard that they guilt trip their employees. Who does that? I love shopping at City market for quick pick ups, but u can't help to find myself seeing managers mistreating these employees. As a result, the employees underperform and creates aisle clogs. Don't get me wrong I do not like to acknowledge the "behind the scenes" of management, but if this is management then there is something wrong with Aspen's city market.
Nice market right in the middle of town. Isle ways are a little tight but staff was very helpful. Great selections and a perfect deli. A must stop if you’re in town for a while and need groceries.

Small location but solid selection. The prices are reasonable and City Market doesn't spike up the prices just because it's located in Aspen. Only complaints is that because it is small is that it's usually always crowded, although the lines move pretty fast. Store seems a little outdated too if you pay attention to the flooring and shelving.
Quick, had a good selection, including a fast n reasonable ready to eat dinner takeout option.
Very nice people,  reasonable prices.  Good selection
